title.narrative: OUTPUT 5.5 CHILD PROTECTION IN EMERGENCIES

description.narrative: Output 5 (Child Protection in emergencies): Government and humanitarian actors at national and subnational level have improved capacity to prevent, mitigate, prepare for and respond to child protection in emergencies in a timely and coordinated manner., which contributes to Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Prevention Of Harmful Practice (Covid), Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys are progressively empowered and protected from violence, exploitation, neglect and harmful practices by functioning, quality child protection systems and positive social norms at national and subnational level including in humanitarian settings.

description.narrative: UNICEF continued supporting the development of a contingency plan and capacity building for child protection in emergency and specifically advocated for the inclusion of refugees in national policies and programmes in partnership with UNHCR. In collaboration with the Ministry of Women’s Empowerment and Child Protection (MOWECP), UNICEF ensured prompt and tailored interventions in response to protection issues related to the COVID-19 pandemic. UNICEF supported the vulnerability mapping and registration of children affected by COVID-19-associated orphanhood using RapidPro as well as providing technical support and capacity building for the national and subnational coordination mechanism for services.; | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:30/11/2021
